Jim Taliadoros
A business-facing Full Stack Developer (with some Dev Ops), with extensive experience in Agile environments delivering solutions for Banking, Finance and Media corporations from conception to delivery using the Angular, MVC, Restful API, Azure and SQL Tech stacks. Well versed in SOLID coding best practices and building robust solutions with architectural patterns such as DDD (Domain Driver Design) and CQRS amongst others. Highlights include full stack greenfield experience at Rabobank, and UBS in a development capacity, and UK Equities experience in a business capacity working on the trading floors (dealing assistant) at Credit Suisse. Outside of work, Keep up to date with current technological trends via a subscription to Pluralsight courses and books. Firm believer in Lean Startup principles.

Technical Summary
As a full stack web developer with over 18 years development experience I have gained commercial experience with countless numbers of tools, languages, patterns and methodologies. The list is too long to reproduce here, so instead I have listed those which I believe are current and relevant to today's development landscape.





Currently Studying:  Blazor, Azure Cognitive Services

Company: Rabobank    Industry: Banking
Date: April 2018 - May 2020 (2 Years 1 Month)

Role Summary: Full Stack Senior Developer using all components listed above, and some Dev Ops support

Project Summary: GCOB (Global Client Onboarding) was a Greenfield project, building a Know Your Client (KYC) onboarding system for the bank. Project was built to tight deadlines using agile principles (Scrum & Testing/Deployment pipelines) to facilitate the delivery of new functionality to end users in 2 week cycles.

Regulatory software systems require designs that have domain robustness built into its core. For this reason the system was built using Domain Driven Design to ensure that at all points in time the data captured by the system was true to the Banks Regulatory Business Rules and also gave a true representation of facts relating to the client case being worked on.

Building quality software also requires putting checks in place to ensure that new development does not inadvertently break the existing domain rules. This was achieved with a full suite of Unit, Integration and Acceptance tests for both the front and back end.

Agile projects with short delivery cycles are underpinned by robust delivery pipelines. To this end the Team was responsible for building and managing development pipelines to development, testing and production environments using Azure Dev Ops.

Company: PwC  - (PriceWaterhouseCoopers)    Industry: Accounting & Finance
Date: March 2015 - November 2017 (2 Years 9 Months)

Role Summary: Full Stack Lead/Senior Developer, Requirements gathering with business, System Design.

Technology Utilised: First iteration of the Web Portal consisted of AngularJS Single Page Application, consuming ASP.Net Web API 2 Restful Web Services and a SQL Server Database. Window services where used for data extraction into QlikView, a 3rd party data visualization tool. For authentication Auth0, and later OAuth2. The solution was coded using the CQRS design pattern with a TDD approach taken.  As the project matured the solution was migrated onto the cloud with a refactor to a microservice design, using ASP.Net Core, targeting  .net framework, NoSQL Azure Storage, RabbitMQ to deal with messaging between different components.

Company: Cannes Lions Festivals  Industry: Advertising
Date: August 2013 - February 2015 (1 Year 6 Months)

Development of a new SPA (single page application) festivals delegate booking system using AngularJS, MVC Web Api Restful services. Azure storage was used for storing delegate booking documentation. Work was also required to re-architect the legacy backend booking and finance database layers to reduce the number of databases used.

Company: UBS (Switzerland) Industry: Investment Banking
Date: July 2010 - July -2013 (3 Years)

Role Summary: Full Stack Senior Developer, Business Requirements Analysis,  Scrum Guidance

The project: Based in Zurich, Switzerland. Developed an internal system to audit the bank's internal software systems, identify those that held client data, and determine whether any systems violated current country client data jurisdiction rules. As the initial developer I helped recruit additional developers. I provide dthe team with guidance on scrum. Full project lifecycle. The solution consisted of a of front end web MVC / Ajax web application,  a number of back end window services and web services that interfaced with internal UBS software inventory systems. A major part of the web solution was the building of a rules based engine for determining which data capture fields to present to users of the web application, based on previous answers submitted.

Estates Gazette is a leading UK publication for the Commercial Property Sector. We migrated Egi’s commercial property portal onto the .net framework, and condensed a number of standalone websites and databases into a single portal with a much more simplified user search UI.

XPertHR Benchmarking is a leading tool used within the HR function of companies which provides ‘employee benefit’ comparison services for companies across varying industries and sectors. The project scope was to improve system response times by introducing SQL Data warehouses into the architecture for reporting queries. This required the wholesale refactoring of the data access, business and service layers.
